Axis-Shield Investors Say Alere Bid Too Low, Sunday Times Says

-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 
2011-09-04T08:44:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-04/axis-shield-investors-say-alere-bid-too-low-sunday-times-says.html
     Sept. 4 (Bloomberg) -- Axis-Shield Plc (ASD)  investors said Alere
Inc.’s bid of 460 pence a share undervalues the health-care
company, the  Sunday Times reported , citing investors Kenneth Andersen of Home Capital AS and Ole Soeberg of Skagen A/S.  Home Capital’s Andersen owns 4.3 percent of Axis-Shield and
Skagen’s Soeberg holds 7.5 percent, according to data compiled
by Bloomberg. Alere declined to say if it would increase its
offer, the Sunday Times reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Martin in London at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Armstrong  at 
 Parmstrong10@bloomberg.net  